column1: # Different Neutrophil signatures derived from comparison of Neutrophils with all other clusters
# and by comparing TANs with NANs.
# neutro_sig: These are genes highly specific for the Neutrophil cluster in primary tumor samples
# neutro_sig2: These genes are a subset of the above. They are fewer
# neutro_sig3: Only the canonical marker gene
#   These are genes relatively specific for TANs vs. NANs and all other cell-types based on single-cell data
#   from primary tumor and normal adjacent data
#   These are the top genes differentially expressed between TANs and NANs
#   They are not necessarily specific for the Neutrophil cluster.
